FBIS3-56445 "drsov011_b_94032" FBIS-SOV-94-011 Document Type:Daily Report 18 Jan 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political Issues Fedorov on `Beginning of Changes' LD1701085394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0803 GMT 17 Jan 94 LD1701085394 Moscow ITAR-TASS Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Moscow January 17 TASS -- Russia's Finance Minister Boris Fedorov said he understood First Vice-Premier Yegor Gaydar's decision to resign from the government, announced on Sunday [16 January]. The government's last decisions indicate the "beginning of changes", Fedorov pointed out in an interview with the "Echo of Moscow" radio station. "I did not have any advance notice of Yegor Gaydar's intention", Fedorov said. He said he had not yet got an invitation to join the reshuffled government. If such a proposal is made, he will make a decision on Monday or Thursday, Fedorov added.
